Xedges.info: Edges in reconstructed nuclear recoil energy [keV]-- the binwise likelihood is computed in bins from these edges (and the migration matrix has the same edges)
Xedges.title: Reconstructed NR recoil energy

Yedges.info: The binwise likelihood is computed for a range of signals (here from 0 to 3). For plotting convenience, the edges are written so that the center of each bin corresponds to the signal for which the binwise likelihood was computed.
Yedges.title: Signal Expectation

Z.info: Binwise likelihood computed in bins of reconstructed energy (1st axis), as function of true signal expected in that bin (2nd axes). See paper for details of interpreting this object.
Z.title: $\lambda_\mathrm{bin}(s)$
